<ServiceHero
  title="Built-In Refrigerator Repair Across Southern California"
  subtitle="Same-day across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino & Riverside counties. Sub-Zero · Liebherr · Thermador · Miele · Viking · GE Monogram · True column built-in. Panel-ready and integrated units. BHGS Licensed #A49573. $89 diagnostic."
  heroImageTitle="Built-In Refrigerator Repair"
/>

<!-- INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01, About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Built-in refrigerators are a different repair than freestanding models. The access, the components, and the approach are all different.</h2>

        <p>A freestanding refrigerator can be pulled away from the wall for rear access, that's how most appliance technicians approach standard refrigerator repair. A built-in refrigerator is installed flush with the surrounding cabinetry and ventilates through the front grille. It cannot be moved. All service is done from the front, through the interior, or by carefully removing the unit from its cabinet housing, a process that requires experience with the specific brand's installation system to avoid damaging the surrounding cabinetry.</p>

        <p>Southern California has one of the highest concentrations of luxury built-in refrigerators in the US. Sub-Zero, Liebherr, Thermador, Miele, Viking, GE Monogram, and True Residential column built-ins are standard equipment in kitchens across LA's luxury core (Bel Air, Brentwood, Beverly Hills, Pacific Palisades, Malibu, the Hollywood Hills), Orange County's coastal luxury (Newport Coast, Pelican Hill, Newport Beach, Laguna Beach), Ventura County's Conejo Valley (Westlake Village, Hidden Hills-adjacent, Calabasas-Westlake corridor), and the Inland Empire's wine-country and estate markets (Temecula, Rancho Cucamonga estates, Riverside hills), these are $8,000–$25,000+ appliances designed for 20-year service lives with proper maintenance. When something fails, repair is almost always the right decision, and it requires a technician who knows these specific systems. Same-day service across all five counties, BHGS Licensed #A49573.</p>

        <!-- CONDENSER CHECK -->
        <div class="condenser-block">
          <div class="c-label">🔧 Sub-Zero Owners, Check This First</div>
          <h3>The condenser is the most overlooked maintenance item on any Sub-Zero</h3>
          <p>Sub-Zero built-ins have a vacuum condenser that must be cleaned every 12 months. When it accumulates dust and debris, the compressor overheats and the refrigerator loses cooling capacity, the most common "not cooling" complaint on Sub-Zero units. The condenser is accessed through the front kick grille at the bottom of the unit.</p>
          <p>Remove the kick grille, and use a vacuum with a brush attachment to clean the condenser coils. If the refrigerator resumes normal cooling within 24 hours, the condenser was the issue, and you've saved a service call. If cooling doesn't improve, or if you're seeing error codes on the display, call us at {phone}.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="sticky-cta">
        <div class="cta-label">Built-In Refrigerator Repair</div>
        <a href={phoneHref} class="cta-phone">{phone}</a>
        <a href={phoneHref} class="btn-cta">Call Now, Same Day</a>
